cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.NA, cs.CC, cs.DC 

This paper deals with a convex optimization problem that arises in machine learning and computer science. It proposes an algorithm that runs in time dependent on the matrix multiplication exponent and dual exponent, which are topics in numerical linear algebra (cs.NA). The paper also introduces a data structure to maintain the central path of interior point methods, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS). The algorithm proposed in the paper is a central path method, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the problem of empirical risk minimization is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
